 183:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c **** /**
 184:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @brief  isp_ae_get_new_exposure
 185:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         This function computes the new sensor exposure to be applied
 186:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         for a given lux and a given luminance target
 187:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         This function is implemented in accordance with the exposure estimation
 188:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         principles based on the estimated lux value of the current scene.
 189:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         There are 3 models of new sensor exposure estimation used in this AE algorithm:
 190:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - Estimation 1 is used for values above ­ØÉ┐­Øæó­Øæź­Øæģ­ØæÆ­Øæō_­ØÉ╗­ØÉ┐
 191:../Drivers/ISP/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - Estimation 2 is used for values below ­ØÉ┐­Øæó­Øæź­Øæģ­ØæÆ­Øæō_­ØÉ╗­ØÉ┐ and above ­Øæ
